HEADWORD: Graphitic
<hw>Gra*phit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to,
containing, derived from, or resembling, graphite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Graphitic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an
organic acid, so called because obtained by the oxidation of graphite;
-- usually called <altname>mellitic acid</altname>.</cd> --
<col><b>Graphitic carbon</b></col>, <cd>in iron or steel, that portion
of the carbon which is present as graphite.</cd>
<rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj></cs></p>

<p><ent>Graphitoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Graphitoid</ent>⟦br⟧
